cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper is about image super-resolution using deep learning techniques, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the trade-off between distortion and perceptual quality, which involves analyzing the performance of the model and optimizing it, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also uses a generative adversarial network (GAN) framework, which is a popular technique in computer graphics (cs.MM) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed method to single image super-resolution, which falls under graphics (cs.GR).
